      "Text": "Security update for Linux Kernel Live Patch 6 for SLE 12 SP1",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for the Linux Kernel 3.12.59-60_45 fixes one issue.\n\nThe following security bug was fixed:\n\n- CVE-2017-5970: The ipv4_pktinfo_prepare function in net/ipv4/ip_sockglue.c in the Linux kernel allowed attackers to cause a denial of service (system crash) via (1) an application that made crafted system calls or possibly (2) IPv4 traffic with invalid IP options (bsc#1025013).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
